WEBVTT

00:04.770 --> 00:08.656
Good morning.

00:08.877 --> 00:31.474
Let's take our Bibles this morning and we're going to

00:31.842 --> 00:34.786
get into Psalm 23 and look at just verse 1.

00:36.228 --> 00:38.572
Before we do that, I just want to have a time of prayer.

00:38.952 --> 00:40.755
Bill Gurney is the owner of this building.

00:40.815 --> 00:43.038
A tremendous man of God loves Jesus.

00:44.120 --> 00:46.443
He and I are getting to know each other more and more.

00:46.504 --> 00:49.268
He stopped in yesterday and he loves all of the changes.

00:49.288 --> 00:52.492
I don't know if you noticed the changes in the entryway and also the coffee station.

00:53.394 --> 00:54.756
So he came in and took a peek.

00:55.196 --> 01:01.746
He was here doing some other things and he was just excited about what was going on here in our church.

01:01.922 --> 01:03.104
this campus.

01:03.665 --> 01:10.655
But he did mention that his wife who had been battling cancer is having a resurgence of it, a struggle with it.

01:11.676 --> 01:15.021
I said, do you mind if I bring that to the church to pray?

01:15.081 --> 01:16.303
And he's like, absolutely.

01:16.323 --> 01:17.364
He's such a prayer warrior.

01:17.925 --> 01:20.709
So remember Bill Gurney and his wife in prayer.

01:20.729 --> 01:21.530
We're going to pray for them.

01:22.332 --> 01:26.738
We're also going to have some prayer here, too, about people who might have a physical affliction.

01:27.659 --> 01:29.522
You might have something going on in your world.

01:30.050 --> 01:33.415
that's manifesting in the physical dimension.

01:34.176 --> 01:35.578
And so we want to pray for you too.

01:36.139 --> 01:39.443
But before we do even that, so think about that if that is you.

01:39.564 --> 01:41.306
So something physical going on with you.

01:42.788 --> 01:43.910
We need some encouragement.

01:45.031 --> 01:46.554
Does anybody need encouragement today?

01:46.614 --> 01:48.757
Are you a good encourager?

01:48.977 --> 01:49.798
I hope that you are.

01:49.878 --> 01:51.421
We're supposed to encourage one another.

01:51.821 --> 01:55.186
That's part of being in a fellowship or a community of believers.

01:55.778 --> 01:57.080
And so here's what I want you to do.

01:57.200 --> 02:01.605
I want you to think about something very, very encouraging to say to someone else.

02:03.968 --> 02:07.392
Okay, some of you are processors like me, so it'll take me about a week to think of something.

02:08.113 --> 02:08.934
We don't have a whole week.

02:09.755 --> 02:10.936
We have a couple of moments here.

02:10.976 --> 02:13.099
So think about something that you can encourage.

02:13.179 --> 02:14.200
It could be just one word.

02:15.902 --> 02:16.884
It could be a little phrase.

02:16.944 --> 02:18.786
It could be a thought and a Bible verse.

02:18.806 --> 02:20.448
What is that that might be coming to your mind?

02:23.291 --> 02:24.052
Are you getting something?

02:24.173 --> 02:25.394
Raise your hand if you're getting something.

02:26.082 --> 02:27.364
Think of something, think of something.

02:31.491 --> 02:34.356
Okay, whatever the Lord is giving you, because that's from the Lord, you know that, right?

02:35.978 --> 02:37.160
Say it to the person near you.

02:37.641 --> 02:39.705
You're saying, I don't know who that is.

02:40.746 --> 02:41.648
Say it to them anyway.

02:42.529 --> 02:43.571
Go ahead, just say it to them.

02:44.072 --> 02:46.536
Lean over, lean back, turn around, whatever it may be.

02:46.576 --> 02:49.040
And just speak that word of life into them.

02:49.080 --> 02:50.422
Bring that encouragement to them.

02:51.464 --> 02:52.626
People need encouragement.

02:55.138 --> 02:57.360
Don't make fun of the person, actually, that's not the point of this.

02:58.982 --> 03:00.704
Don't tell them they don't match or whatever.

03:00.744 --> 03:04.108
This is supposed to be encouragement.

03:06.090 --> 03:12.777
You see, when the church gets together, there's a lot of times where you sit in the chair, look at the person's back of their head, and there's no interaction.

03:12.837 --> 03:14.179
The body is supposed to come together.

03:15.300 --> 03:18.743
This is what they did in the early church, and we're losing some of that.

03:18.804 --> 03:24.850
So that's why I like to try to encourage and even motivate for us to act a little bit differently than

03:25.186 --> 03:38.139
what might be happening in the modern church, because there's some great things happening in the modern church, but there's some things that need some adjustments and some reform, and some of that is the way we interact.

03:38.159 --> 03:45.846
And so, Holy Spirit might give you something to say to somebody else by the end of our service together, and I would encourage you to go up to them, even if you might not know them.

03:47.688 --> 03:54.034
And there's always a risk with a lot of that, because some people think they need to be the church police, and that's not what I'm saying.

03:55.458 --> 04:00.646
It's not our business really to do a lot of that, but it is our business to encourage one another.

04:01.988 --> 04:05.794
And so if you get something from the Holy Spirit, let somebody know.

04:06.975 --> 04:08.177
Don't leave without telling them.

04:10.280 --> 04:12.263
I remember years ago, the Lord gave me a word.

04:12.303 --> 04:19.314
I wasn't a pastor at the time and I was going to a church and just helping out where I could and things like that.

04:19.374 --> 04:21.938
And the Holy Spirit gave me a word and I said, I don't know if I can say that.

04:22.690 --> 04:24.012
I didn't even know if I wanna say that.

04:24.072 --> 04:25.854
I mean, my life feels pretty crummy right now.

04:26.235 --> 04:27.937
Who am I to say something to somebody else?

04:28.798 --> 04:36.368
And I went and the Holy Spirit was so prompting me that I did go up to this gentleman and I said what the Lord gave me and it just brought tears to his eyes.

04:36.428 --> 04:38.010
You could tell it was a Holy Ghost moment.

04:38.871 --> 04:40.353
You could tell that God was in it.

04:42.195 --> 04:44.218
Let's be open to the move of God like that.

04:44.398 --> 04:44.658
Amen?

04:45.519 --> 04:46.981
Let's do that together.

04:47.001 --> 04:49.745
All right, so who has a physical, something that's going on in your world?

04:50.045 --> 04:50.706
Raise your hand.

04:50.882 --> 04:52.524
something that's afflicting you physically.

04:52.764 --> 04:54.326
Thank you, thank you, thank you, thank you.

04:54.826 --> 04:56.027
Can we put a hand on there?

04:56.428 --> 05:00.292
And if you want to get up out of your chair and go lay hands on them, that's certainly okay.

05:00.492 --> 05:02.354
Lift your hand again, don't be nervous, don't be shy.

05:02.374 --> 05:07.459
If you could, could you start moving and putting some hands over here, over there on the, there's third people.

05:07.879 --> 05:08.800
Thank you, anybody over here?

05:09.081 --> 05:10.582
Need room for something physical.

05:12.064 --> 05:14.907
All right, remember Bill Gurney's wife who's struggling with cancer.

05:15.968 --> 05:16.528
Let's do that.

05:17.209 --> 05:18.290
Jesus, you're the healer.

05:18.626 --> 05:21.930
You are the God who is the God of all comfort.

05:22.671 --> 05:24.674
And you know exactly what you're doing with our lives.

05:25.395 --> 05:34.007
And I don't understand all of why you allow certain things to happen in the area of physical afflictions, whether it be diagnoses or whatever it may be.

05:34.227 --> 05:35.348
It could be very severe.

05:35.368 --> 05:36.109
It could be minor.

05:36.370 --> 05:39.294
Nothing is to be beyond your touch.

05:40.015 --> 05:40.996
Even a prayer to you.

05:41.236 --> 05:42.838
Some people are thinking, oh, it's just so small.

05:42.858 --> 05:43.379
It's so small.

05:43.920 --> 05:44.821
No, it's not small.

05:45.862 --> 05:47.384
It's something that you want us to bring to you.

05:47.404 --> 05:48.626
And so we bring it to you, Lord.

05:49.058 --> 06:04.181
that you would heal, that you would do an amazing work, even now as we're laying hands on and praying for each other, Lord, would you do something that would only be attributed to a move of your spirit, that would only be attributed to a work of God in response to prayer.

06:04.241 --> 06:08.107
And so, Lord, we pray for these people that lift up their hands.

06:10.230 --> 06:18.002
This is what you do, Lord, you save people from their sins, but you also heal bodies, you heal minds, you heal emotions, you heal relationships,

06:18.658 --> 06:19.879
And so we bring all of that to you.

06:19.939 --> 06:23.383
Bill Gurney, Lord, asking for prayer for his dear wife going through this battle again.

06:24.264 --> 06:26.606
And their whole family, God, would you just show up in power?

06:27.126 --> 06:29.889
Would you do something that, again, can only be attributed to you?

06:30.169 --> 06:30.990
He trusts you, Lord.

06:31.050 --> 06:31.871
They all do.

06:32.552 --> 06:33.272
They believe in you.

06:33.593 --> 06:34.273
They trust you.

06:35.334 --> 06:36.295
We cover them in prayer.

06:36.716 --> 06:42.542
For pieces of past is understanding that you would be the comfort that they need, the presence of God.

06:42.642 --> 06:45.404
So real to them in the midst of this struggle.

06:46.365 --> 06:47.026
Yes, Lord.

06:48.002 --> 06:51.287
Help us to understand Psalm 23, verse one, Holy Spirit.

06:51.367 --> 06:58.056
You wrote it through David and help us to apply it and experience it in Jesus' mighty name.

06:58.076 --> 06:59.959
And God's people say, amen.

07:00.880 --> 07:02.602
All right, let's open God's word together.

07:02.642 --> 07:06.147
This is a series we're titling, experiencing Psalm 23.

07:07.209 --> 07:13.938
And I don't have to tell you that all of life is full of a myriad of experiences, a lot of emotion.

07:14.690 --> 07:20.778
And so what we're going to see is that David was a man of expression of emotion experientially.

07:21.979 --> 07:28.488
Experiencing life is full of these kinds of expressions of emotions, motions of joy, caution, of an even fear.

07:29.690 --> 07:32.073
Some of you might be facing some of these right now.

07:32.153 --> 07:37.760
David was a man like this, and he wrote Psalm 23 out of his own experiences.

07:38.741 --> 07:42.386
We have to understand that this was real life to David when he wrote the Psalms.

07:43.426 --> 07:45.829
Psalm 23 is written in this context.

07:47.031 --> 07:48.553
We want to understand that context.

07:50.216 --> 07:53.400
I've titled this second message in our series, how to be sure of your shepherd.

07:53.801 --> 07:55.724
You need to be sure that God is your shepherd.

07:56.745 --> 08:07.901
You need to be sure that he cares for you, that he's concerned about you, that he's walking with you, that he's involved in your life, that he sees what you're going through, how to be sure of your shepherd.

08:08.242 --> 08:10.325
Psalm 23 verse one, what's it say?

08:10.345 --> 08:11.346
Can we say it out loud?

08:11.522 --> 08:15.146
The Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.

08:16.548 --> 08:18.831
The Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.

08:18.951 --> 08:20.072
How can we be sure of anything?

08:22.015 --> 08:24.117
How can you be sure that that chair is going to hold you up?

08:25.599 --> 08:25.799
Right?

08:25.899 --> 08:29.043
You stopped at Dunkin' Donuts, had that Boston cream on the way to church, right?

08:30.245 --> 08:32.067
And you're thinking, oh, I got way too many pounds here.

08:32.147 --> 08:33.188
It might not hold me up.

08:33.208 --> 08:36.712
How do you know and be sure that your car is going to bring you home safely?

08:36.753 --> 08:41.298
How do you know and are sure or assured of that your health is going to be good in the coming year?

08:41.794 --> 08:45.698
How do you know anything for sure or anyone for sure?

08:47.921 --> 08:50.944
In the area of salvation, this is called the doctrine of assurance.

08:51.024 --> 09:04.039
I was talking to some people, many people through the years that struggle with the doctrine of assurance, that they are truly born again, that they know Jesus, that Jesus knows them, that they walk with God, they lack the doctrine of assurance.

09:05.841 --> 09:10.706
We are to be sure, the Apostle John said, that we have this hope within us.

09:11.970 --> 09:21.582
And so if you're someone that battles with assurance or being sure of your shepherd, then I pray that today's message will help you to get to a better place of being sure of your shepherd.

09:21.722 --> 09:22.143
Are you ready?

09:23.644 --> 09:25.727
The doctrine of assurance or being sure.

09:26.288 --> 09:31.114
I have doubted God's presence in my life through my pain often, often.

09:31.494 --> 09:33.416
More in the earlier years of my Christian life.

09:33.897 --> 09:37.341
And what we're going to see in the life of David is something that transformed him.

09:37.722 --> 09:41.266
That's why he could write Psalm 23 1.

09:41.890 --> 09:45.174
He had to go through some things to get to that place as I have and you have.

09:47.657 --> 09:55.146
The devil wants us to doubt that God really has saved us and made us his own, that we are truly the sheep of his pasture.

09:55.887 --> 09:58.970
And David had to wrestle out some of these same struggles that you and I do.

09:59.471 --> 10:05.298
And to get to the place of understanding God as a sure shepherd, then we have to go to places that David went to.

10:06.498 --> 10:10.762
We're going to have to get into his life as recorded in the scripture, understand what he was going through.

10:11.123 --> 10:16.549
And then out of that, how was he able to say, the Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.

10:20.012 --> 10:22.895
There are two areas I want to look at with you, conflicts and crises.

10:23.816 --> 10:25.918
Where are some of the conflicts that David struggled with?

10:25.958 --> 10:27.960
Where are some of the crises that David went through?

10:28.001 --> 10:29.782
Again, here's the secret.

10:30.864 --> 10:32.305
Let's walk with him for a moment.

10:32.345 --> 10:33.266
Would you go with me?

10:34.562 --> 10:40.168
To do that, we're going to have to go to some things that David experienced, and you're going to follow me with that.

10:40.248 --> 10:41.088
I'm sure you will.

10:41.149 --> 10:43.311
To 1 Samuel chapter 18.

10:43.331 --> 10:45.173
1 Samuel 18.

10:45.313 --> 10:46.874
You're saying, is that in the New Testament?

10:46.894 --> 10:47.835
Where is 1 Samuel?

10:48.896 --> 10:49.977
That's in our Old Testament.

10:50.798 --> 10:52.620
Let's go to 1 Samuel chapter 18.

10:52.640 --> 10:55.042
I want to look at verses 1 down to verse 12 with you.

10:55.483 --> 11:02.770
I'm going to do a commentary on this, make some thoughts, and we'll see what was happening in the life of David in the area of conflict.

11:05.442 --> 11:07.325
Maybe you'll find yourself here in some way.

11:07.345 --> 11:15.938
1 Samuel chapter 18 verse 1, the Bible says, as soon as he had finished speaking to Saul.

11:16.558 --> 11:17.400
You remember King Saul?

11:18.642 --> 11:23.429
The son of Jonathan was knit to his soul, the soul of David, and Jonathan loved him as his own soul.

11:23.889 --> 11:25.512
Verse 2, and Saul took him that day.

11:26.032 --> 11:29.778
Would not let him return to his father's house, then Jonathan made a covenant with David.

11:30.274 --> 11:31.996
because he loved him as his own soul.

11:32.076 --> 11:33.859
What a relationship the both of them had.

11:34.179 --> 11:36.162
Some people think that it was homosexuality.

11:36.202 --> 11:37.764
Believe it or not, can you imagine that interpretation?

11:39.206 --> 11:39.547
It's evil.

11:40.929 --> 11:41.950
It's wrong interpretation.

11:41.970 --> 11:46.296
This is a very close, bonded friendship that these two men had.

11:46.797 --> 11:50.382
Verse 4, Jonathan stripped himself of the robe that was on him and gave it to David.

11:50.963 --> 11:53.506
And his armor and even his sword and his bow and his belt.

11:53.947 --> 11:59.314
And David went out and was successful wherever Saul sent him, so that Saul sent him over the men of war.

11:59.490 --> 12:03.335
And this was good in the sight of all the people and also in the sight of Saul's servants.

12:04.236 --> 12:14.008
Verse six, and as they were coming home when David returned from striking down the Philistine, the women came out of all the cities of Israel singing and dancing to meet King Saul.

12:15.089 --> 12:23.980
Picture this situation here where all of these people are celebrating the victories and these women come and it says that he came to meet with dancing King Saul.

12:24.961 --> 12:27.484
Can you imagine what was going through the mind of King Saul at that moment?

12:28.565 --> 12:29.266
This is great.

12:30.274 --> 12:31.877
He's feeling really good at this point, right?

12:34.802 --> 12:45.601
Since they had tambourine songs of joy with musical instruments and the women came saying to one another as they celebrated, Saul has struck down his thousands and David, his ten thousands.

12:46.041 --> 12:47.444
All of a sudden, what happens to King Saul?

12:48.686 --> 12:49.247
Not so good.

12:51.731 --> 12:51.952
Right?

12:51.992 --> 12:52.933
Well, what happens to him?

12:53.474 --> 12:55.538
Verse 8, and Saul was very angry.

12:57.570 --> 13:01.035
And this saying displeased to me, said, they have ascribed to David 10,000.

13:01.055 --> 13:02.917
And to me, they have ascribed thousands.

13:03.538 --> 13:06.082
And what more can he have but the kingdom?

13:06.702 --> 13:09.286
And saw I, David, from that day on.

13:09.987 --> 13:16.656
Listen, when somebody eyes you from that day on, you're going to understand conflict like you've never understood it before.

13:17.197 --> 13:18.018
And you're saying, what do you mean?

13:18.358 --> 13:20.521
Well, Saul was jealous of David.

13:21.002 --> 13:21.783
This is what happened.

13:22.504 --> 13:27.090
And so from that day on, for almost 20 years, Saul would pursue David to try to kill him.

13:28.386 --> 13:32.049
There are going to be people in conflicts in our world where people are going to come against you.

13:32.390 --> 13:33.671
They're going to eye you a certain way.

13:33.691 --> 13:35.052
Have we gotten an eye from somebody?

13:36.173 --> 13:37.214
This is very interesting.

13:37.254 --> 13:42.820
Now, after church, after our service, you're going to be like looking at everybody, looking for the eye, right, the stink eye.

13:43.020 --> 13:43.921
I call it the stink eye.

13:45.542 --> 13:47.084
And so they're going to give you the up and down.

13:47.124 --> 13:50.247
They're going to give you the left and right, right?

13:50.267 --> 13:51.808
And they're not going to do it to encourage you.

13:51.828 --> 13:58.034
They're going to do it because inside of their heart they look at you and they're jealous of your look, of your confidence,

13:58.242 --> 14:00.906
of your success, of your position.

14:02.949 --> 14:10.882
And from that day on, that relationship between you and them could potentially erupt into something very similar to King Saul and David.

14:11.703 --> 14:14.127
This isn't just something that they would have experienced.

14:14.147 --> 14:15.690
You're thinking, that's not going to touch my life.

14:16.090 --> 14:16.992
It's going to touch your life.

14:17.052 --> 14:17.493
Trust me.

14:20.017 --> 14:21.379
It shouldn't happen, but it does.

14:22.921 --> 14:25.906
David is in a conflict here that lasted a long

14:26.018 --> 14:26.900
long time.

14:26.960 --> 14:28.523
He was stalked by King Saul.

14:29.164 --> 14:30.747
At times David would live in caves.

14:30.807 --> 14:33.151
I did a series many years ago called Caved Wellers.

14:33.892 --> 14:36.737
We all have to learn how to live in caves at times.

14:37.960 --> 14:42.748
That's a hard place to live when you're being pursued by someone that's threatened by you, jealous of you.

14:42.768 --> 14:45.874
They want to take you down, take you out.

14:48.258 --> 14:50.481
Well, a lot of this has to do with our response.

14:50.561 --> 14:51.423
Now, this is important.

14:51.463 --> 14:53.486
So this conflict is then in David's life.

14:53.526 --> 14:55.249
It's going to be in our life in various forms.

14:55.289 --> 14:58.293
Maybe not this severe, but it's going to be in our lives.

14:58.353 --> 15:03.241
And the choices that we then make in reaction to something like this is very important.

15:03.301 --> 15:05.544
Go to chapter 24 for Samuel.

15:06.305 --> 15:09.490
Here's the situation that David has put to the test.

15:10.338 --> 15:13.161
And all along, David's learning how to be shepherded by God.

15:13.201 --> 15:14.242
And this is how it happens.

15:14.302 --> 15:15.563
It happens in our conflicts.

15:15.944 --> 15:25.454
If you're going to look for a life of ease that has no conflict, and I'm not saying you bring it on yourself, I'm just saying that if you're living for Jesus and you're following Him close, there's going to be some conflict.

15:26.054 --> 15:31.300
But all of that is used of the Lord to help us to understand that He shepherds us in the middle of all of that.

15:31.320 --> 15:37.426
I don't even know if we can learn the shepherding heart of God if we don't go through conflict and crises.

15:38.786 --> 15:48.736
Well, here's something that David is experiencing here in verses one to seven that his reaction is very important as yours is and mine is when this happens to us.

15:48.756 --> 15:54.001
When Saul returned from following the Philistines, verse one, he was told behold, David is in the wilderness of Engedi.

15:54.842 --> 16:00.767
Then Saul took 3,000 chosen men out of all of Israel and went to seek David and his men in front of the wild goats rocks.

16:01.488 --> 16:07.794
And he came to the sheepfold by the way where there was a cave and Saul went in to relieve himself.

16:09.282 --> 16:11.685
Okay, basically he's going in to go number two.

16:13.488 --> 16:14.168
That's what's happening.

16:15.931 --> 16:17.833
Because I know some people are thinking, what's going on here?

16:17.893 --> 16:19.075
Let's just lay it out there, right?

16:20.777 --> 16:26.124
So he goes in there and he's gonna relieve himself, go to the bathroom, and he's in this cave.

16:26.645 --> 16:29.148
And David's in the cave with his men, right?

16:29.188 --> 16:33.714
This is what he goes on to say, notice now, David and his men were sitting in the innermost parts of the cave.

16:33.954 --> 16:39.021
And the men of David said to him, here's the day in which the Lord said to you, behold, I will give your enemy into your hand.

16:39.401 --> 16:45.509
And you shall do to him, fully cut off a corner of Saul's robe.

16:46.170 --> 16:50.937
And afterwards, David's heart struck him because he had cut off a corner of Saul's robe.

16:51.377 --> 16:54.582
And he said to his men, the Lord forbid that I should do this thing to my Lord.

16:54.642 --> 16:59.068
And the Lord's anointed to put out my hand against him, seeing he is the Lord's anointed.

16:59.408 --> 16:59.949
Here's the thing.

17:00.590 --> 17:01.591
David could have killed him.

17:01.671 --> 17:02.532
He's that close.

17:02.552 --> 17:03.954
Saul would have never known what hit him.

17:04.418 --> 17:05.620
And so David's that close.

17:05.640 --> 17:11.831
He cuts off just a corner of the robe, but he holds back in the middle of his conflict, being chased and stalked by King Saul.

17:11.851 --> 17:12.793
He could have ended it.

